article.headline: Wichita State 63, Drake 57
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Fridge Holman scored 13 points while Randy Burns and Aaron Hogg each added 11 points, helping Wichita State hold off upset-minded Drake to earn a 63-57 victory in a Missouri Valley Conference Tournament quarterfinal game Saturday night. No. 3-seeded Wichita State (21-9) will play No. 2-seeded Northern Iowa (19-9) at 5 p.m. Sunday in a semifinal game. The Shockers advanced to the tourney title game last year, losing 70-69 to Creighton. No. 15 Southern Illinois, the top-seeded team, meets No. 5 Southwest Missouri State in a 2:30 p.m. semifinal game. Chaun Brooks paced Drake (12-16) with 12 points. Drake shot just 35 percent from the floor on 20 of 57 shooting. The Bulldogs have lost their last six games played in the quarterfinal round. Drake last won a quarterfinal game in 1993. The Bulldogs led by as many as eight points at 37-29 with 14:29 to play. The Shockers, who made 17 turnovers, took a 45-43 lead after an 8-0 run with 6:25 remaining. Brooks scored to tie it at 45 but the Shockers scored seven unanswered points for a 52-45 lead. Wichita State made 48 percent of its shots and outrebounded Drake 38-31. Drake was able to close the gap to three points twice, the final time at 59-56 after Klayton Korver, who finished with 11 points, hit a 3-pointer with 1:10 to play. Drake led 27-23 at halftime. Neither team shot well with the Bulldogs hitting 31 percent of their shots and the Shockers making 41 percent. Drake connected on 8 of 12 free throws while Wichita State did not attempt a free throw. Drake went without a basket for 7:34 but trailed just 16-13 before Josh Powell scored with 5:55 remaining in the half. After Fridge Holman gave the Shockers a 17-16 lead, the Bulldogs went on an 8-0 run to gain the lead.
